[assistant] Fixed the failing test by avoiding package scanning over Java 21-compiled test classes.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Change made:
[assistant] - Updated `BeanDefinitionLoaderTest.loadsPackageSourceByFindingClassInPackage()` to use an existing Spring Boot package:
[assistant] 
[assistant] ```java
[assistant] new TestSpringApplication().loadInto(context, "org.springframework.boot.admin");
[assistant] 
[assistant] assertThat(Package.getPackage("org.springframework.boot.admin")).isNotNull();
[assistant] ```
[assistant] 
[assistant] - Removed the test-only `PackageScanProbe` package/class that caused Spring Boot 2.6.3’s ASM reader to fail on class file major version `65`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Why this fixes it:
[assistant] - Spring Boot 2.6.3 uses an older ASM version that cannot parse Java 21 test class files during classpath scanning.
[assistant] - Using `org.springframework.boot.admin` exercises `BeanDefinitionLoader.findPackage(...)` against Spring Boot’s own dependency classes instead, which are compiled to a supported bytecode level.
[assistant] - The test still reaches the target dynamic-access call site:
[assistant]   - `Class.forName(...)` in `findPackage(...)`
[assistant] 
